    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I guess I'm just seeing a lot of different perspectives in the news. Some people say it's an economic necessity for aging populations, while others argue it's fundamentally destabilizing to domestic labor markets and social systems. From a purely data-driven standpoint, is there any way to bridge those views, or is one side just ignoring the actual empirical evidence?",
